Meet “Fernando Dior”. The 5 year old boss, aka Mr. Make Them Smile lol❤️. 
We have been searching for the right opportunity for him for years. Any competition we’ve entered him in had always turned out to be a scam that wanted us to pay hundreds of dollars for no reason. 
I found @klamodelmaker on IG a few months ago and I have seen nothing but amazing success stories. I have had so many doubts and stopped trusting people in the industry, but with @klamodelmaker, I can tell that this isn’t a job, this is her passion & I’m open to trusting that she can change the narrative. I want Dior to do whatever his heart desires, and he expressed to me that he wanted to be on tv. So I will do whatever it takes to support him and if he were to ever change his mind, I’ll support that too. It’s not about what “I” want for him. It’s about what makes him happy. I told him we could start by getting him more comfortable on IG and YouTube and I’ve been praying for a great opportunity to come his way.  It’s not just about him being a cute kid, it’s about the light that shines through him and the ability to share that with the world❤️. So we would absolutely love the opportunity to work with @klamodelmaker

This year has been one for the books. 
It’s been the year of “transition” and “transformation”
I’ve learned so much about myself that I didn’t fully understand before. God is really doing some work on me to prepare me for what is to come, but going through it has been the toughest thing I’ve had to deal with as an adult, while still loving and supporting my child who needs the strength of his mommy around the clock. When I think of how my year went, these are a few words to come to mind:
•blessings
•lessons
•gains
•losses
•healing
•brokenness 
•hurt 
•strength 
•vulnerability 
•depression 
•love
•support

And through conversations I’ve had with close friends, clients and family, it’s been a heavy year for everyone.
But we can’t compare our journey to anyone else’s. Because God works on us all individually. 

I’m excited to see what God has planned for my future & yours too❤️

#selflove #selflovejourney #healing #vulnerability #strength #motivation #support #butgod #ministry
Self Appreciation Post because I rarely do it. Lets be great today❤️
